subSubSection.paragraph:
Remarks. Specimens of
P. binotatus
from Odzala resemble the holotype described from the main channel of the Congo River (locality Ikengo,
Fig. 1
) (
Pellegrin, 1924
). However, they also exhibit several differences, mainly in head morphology. The holotype has a larger mouth (HL/MW = 3.2 versus ≥ 4.4 in Odzala specimens), a longer snout (HL/SNL = 5.5 versus ≥ 6.8 in Odzala specimens) and a larger interorbital width (HL/IOW = 2.3 versus ≥ 2.6 in Odzala specimens). Additional comparative material from the type locality and other localities in the Congo basin are necessary to determine the taxonomic implications of these differences.
